[SN]TITLE[SN]
Glenavy farmer given suspended sentence for 'horrendous' animal cruelty case

[SN]FIRST-SENTENCE[SN]
A County Antrim farmer who was the subject of the biggest ever herd seizure in Northern Ireland has been given a suspended sentence for animal cruelty.

[SN]RESTBODY[SN]
12 April 2016 Last updated at 21:19 BST
James Steele, 46, of Gobrana Road in Glenavy, heard a judge say he was "shocked" by the state of animals on his farm.
BBC News NI's agriculture correspondent Conor Macauley reports.
